:
:   PATCH BY JERRY LUCAS TO FIX LOCKUP WITH RNR/RR LOGIC.  FOLLOWING IS
:   A POSSIBLE SCENARIO LEADING TO THE PROBLEM:
:    - NOS RECEIVED FROM NET, SEND RNR TO HOST.
:    - SND RECEIVED FROM NET, ICSND ROUTINE JUMPS TO CWROT. FLAGS ARE SET
:      BUT NO RR IS QUEUED TO RMAKE.
:    - RMAKE IS NEXT IN BGEXEC LOOP, HAS DATA QUEUED UP.  WINROT FLAG IS
:      RESET AT PSUB7E.
:    - ROTWIN IS CALLED BY BGEXEC LOOP, BUT WINROT HAS BEEN RESET IN RMAKE.
:      NO RR WILL BE QUEUED.
:    - CCITT SAYS AN RNR MUST BE CLEARED BY RR, NOT JUST BY DATA CARRYING
:      P(R).  SO WE HANG.
:
:   SUGGESTED FIX IS TO RMAKE.
:
PATCH(891017,1000,JL,PSUB7E,,6)
        J       PA1PTR,,
:
CONPATCH(PA1PTR,,18)
        STB     R2,TPPR,R6,
        TBT     R6,LSTRNR,,
        JN      PSUB7D,,
        J       PSUB7E+6,,              :..CONDITION, DON'T RESET FLAGS
ENDPATCH(FIX POSSIBLE PACKET FLOW CONTROL LOCK-UP)
